== SETI候選和信號報告 ==
在2015年5月15日，一個短暫、單一的11GHz（波長2.7釐米）的電波訊號<ref name="ArsTechnica">{{cite web |last1=Berger |first1=Eric |title=Ars Technica |url=http://arstechnica.com/science/2016/08/seti-has-observed-a-strong-signal-that-may-originate-from-a-sun-like-star/ |website=Ars Technica |publisher=Ars Technica |accessdate=29 August 2016 |archive-date=2019-05-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190511170507/https://arstechnica.com/science/2016/08/seti-has-observed-a-strong-signal-that-may-originate-from-a-sun-like-star/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>被[[拉坦-600|拉坦-600]]電波天文台，包括{{link-en|克勞迪奧·梅肯|Claudio Maccone}}在內的一組科學家觀測到來自HD 164595的方向。這訊號可能是來自地面的電波頻率干擾，或是經由重力透鏡來自更遙遠之處<ref>SETI observations on the RATAN-600 telescope in 2015 and detection of a strong signal in the direction of HD 164595 Bursov N., Filippova L., Filippov V., Gindilis L., Maccone C. et al. 2016 | in "IAA SETI Permanent Committee", Guadalajara, Mexico</ref>。它只被單獨一個團隊，只在單獨一架望遠鏡觀測到一次（歷時2秒鐘），只符合{{link-en|里約等級| Post-detection_policy#Significance_of_transmission}}<ref>{{cite web |title=Rio scale calculator |url=http://avsport.org/IAA/riocalc.htm |access-date=2016-08-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160902040412/http://avsport.org/IAA/riocalc.htm |archive-date=2016-09-02 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>的1（無意義）或2（低）。發現的團隊建議要持久的監測，但是在已經進行的39次觀測，仍然只有這唯一的一次<ref name="A Candidate Signal for SETI">{{cite web |url=http://www.centauri-dreams.org/?p=36248 |title=An Interesting SETI Candidate in Hercules |publisher=Centauri Dreams |date=2016-08-29 |accessdate=29 August 2016 |author=Gilster, Paul |archive-date=2018-01-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180110150834/https://www.centauri-dreams.org/?p=36248 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

這次的觀測定於2016年9月27日在一次科學會議中提出簡報<ref>{{cite web|title=International Astronautical Congress 2016|url=http://www.iafastro.org/events/iac/iac2016/|accessdate=2016-08-31|archive-date=2018-12-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181214034642/http://www.iafastro.org/events/iac/iac2016/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，但Paul Gilster於8月27日它的部落格，半人馬座星夢，提早披漏了這個訊息，過早引起公眾的注意<ref>{{cite news |last1=Gilster |first1=Paul |title=An Interesting SETI Candidate in Hercules |url=http://www.centauri-dreams.org/?p=36248 |accessdate=29 August 2016 |date=27 August 2016 |archive-date=2018-01-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180110150834/https://www.centauri-dreams.org/?p=36248 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Boyle |first1=Alan |title=They’re not saying it’s aliens, but signal traced to sunlike star sparks SETI interest |url=https://www.yahoo.com/tech/not-saying-aliens-signal-traced-194522566.html |accessdate=29 August 2016 |date=29 August 2016 |archive-date=2017-04-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170404203402/https://www.yahoo.com/tech/not-saying-aliens-signal-traced-194522566.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="CNN-20160830">{{cite web |last=Griffiths |first=James |title=Hear me now? 'Strong signal' from sun-like star sparks alien speculation |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/08/30/health/seti-signal-hd-164595-alien-civilization/index.html |date=30 August 2016 |work=[[CNN|CNN]] |accessdate=30 August 2016 |archive-date=2019-05-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190502062227/https://www.cnn.com/2016/08/30/health/seti-signal-hd-164595-alien-civilization/index.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。從2016年8月29日起，媒體的討論引發這個信號可能來自[[卡爾達肖夫指數|第二型文明]]的{{link-en|各向同性燈塔|Isotropic beacon}}的猜測<ref>{{cite news |last1=Seemangal |first1=Robin |title=Not a Drill: SETI Is Investigating a Possible Extraterrestrial Signal From Deep Space |url=http://observer.com/2016/08/not-a-drill-seti-is-investigating-a-possible-extraterrestrial-signal-from-deep-space/ |accessdate=29 August 2016 |date=29 August 2016 |archive-date=2017-12-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171224012147/http://observer.com/2016/08/not-a-drill-seti-is-investigating-a-possible-extraterrestrial-signal-from-deep-space/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Zolfagharifard |first1=Ellie |title=Is Earth being contacted by ALIENS? Mystery radio signals coming from a sun-like star baffle scientists |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sciencetech/article-3763416/Is-Earth-contacted-ALIENS-Mystery-radio-signals-coming-sun-like-star-baffle-scientists.html |accessdate=29 August 2016 |date=29 August 2016 |archive-date=2017-10-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171030222715/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sciencetech/article-3763416/Is-Earth-contacted-ALIENS-Mystery-radio-signals-coming-sun-like-star-baffle-scientists.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。SETI和[[主動搜尋地外文明計劃|METI]]正在使用[[艾倫望遠鏡陣|艾倫望遠鏡陣]]和Boquete Optical SETI做後續的努力<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sfgate.com/local/article/Leaked-space-signal-report-has-SETI-groups-9191169.php |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2016-08-31 |archive-date=2018-01-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180124071611/http://www.sfgate.com/local/article/Leaked-space-signal-report-has-SETI-groups-9191169.php |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="GeekWire">{{Cite web |url=http://www.geekwire.com/2016/signal-seti-interest-hd164595/ |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2016-08-31 |archive-date=2018-04-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180417053944/https://www.geekwire.com/2016/signal-seti-interest-hd164595/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

[[SETI協會|SETI協會]]的資深天文學家{{link-en|賽斯·肖斯塔克|Seth Shostak}}告訴[[GeekWire|GeekWire]]網站說："你真正想要的是另一架望遠鏡的確認，但......這是真的嗎？ 信號可能是真實的，但我懷疑那不是外星人的。這有可能是一個寬頻信號或其他的可能性，它們來自自天然的來源（或甚至地面的干擾）造成<ref name="GeekWire"/>。[[德克薩斯州農工大學|德克薩斯州農工大學]]的天文學家{{link-en|尼可拉斯·桑澤夫|Nicholas Suntzeff}}告訴Ars Technica，信號是軍用頻道的，可能是一顆衛星訊號的下傳，暗示這可能是個需要保密的系統，因此對SETI的科學家而言，都是未知的<ref name="ArsTechnica"/>。

[[加州大學柏克萊分校|加州大學柏克萊分校]]SETI研究中心的科學家<ref>{{cite web |title=Berkeley SETI Research Center |url=http://seti.berkeley.edu |accessdate=2016-08-31 |archive-date=2019-04-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190406232538/http://seti.berkeley.edu/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>使用[[綠堤望遠鏡|綠堤望遠鏡]]觀察HD 164595，只是{{link-en|突破聽|Breakthrough Listen}}計畫的一部分。沒有在拉坦-600報告的位置檢測到暫態頻率的信號<ref>{{cite web |title=Preliminary analysis of star HD 164595 |url=http://seti.berkeley.edu/HD164595_summary.pdf |accessdate=2016-08-31 |archive-date=2018-01-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180124071655/http://seti.berkeley.edu/HD164595_summary.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Breakthrough Listen Follow-up of a Transient Signal from the RATAN-600 Telescope in the Direction of HD 164595 |url=http://seti.berkeley.edu/HD164595.pdf |accessdate=2016-08-31 |archive-date=2019-01-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190112121520/https://seti.berkeley.edu/HD164595.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

